Global investors  bought a  net 419
million rupees ($7.25 million) of Indian equity  derivatives  on
Aug. 24, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 0.7 percent to 1.002 trillion rupees,
according to the exchangeâ€™s  website . Open interest reached a
record 1.6 trillion rupees on Sept. 21, 2010.  Foreign funds bought a net 2.26 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment on Aug.24, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
